The ``text_indentation`` module
======================

Using ``a text printer``
-------------------

This is an example text file in reStructuredText format.  First import
``text_indentation`` from the ``text_indentation`` module:

    >>> text_indentation = __import__('5-text_indentation').text_indentation

Now use it:

    >>> text_indentation('Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur. Hi')
    Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur.
    <BLANKLINE>
    Hi
    >>> text_indentation('My name is Lindsey.')
    My name is Lindsey.
    <BLANKLINE>
    >>> text_indentation('Anna Karenina')
    Anna Karenina
    >>> text_indentation('   ')
    <BLANKLINE>
    >>> text_indentation("")
    <BLANKLINE>
    >>> text_indentation('What.?: Repeat please.')
    What.
    <BLANKLINE>
    ?
    <BLANKLINE>
    :
    <BLANKLINE>
    Repeat please.
    <BLANKLINE>
    >>> text_indentation('Hi\n I\n')
    Hi
    I
    <BLANKLINE>
    >>> text_indentation('Type:\n Computer')
    Type:
    <BLANKLINE>
    <BLANKLINE>
    Computer
    >>> text_indentation('Hey.?   :Girl!')
    Hey.
    <BLANKLINE>
    ?
    <BLANKLINE>
    :
    <BLANKLINE>
    Girl!
